<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-70-0988 </DOCNO><TEXT>Allegations had been made that the Department of Energy was improperlyemploying contractors to assist in lobbying the Congress on nuclear weaponstesting issues. The antilobbying criminal statute has been interpretedby the Department of Justice as allowing federal officials to provideinformation to the Congress and to state their views on proposed legislationbut prohibits &quot;grass-roots&quot; lobbying by federal employees. Thus, DOE'sextensive briefings of congressional Members and staff to influence theirviews on nuclear weapons testing issues did not violate applicable statutoryprovisions.</TEXT></DOC>